       What       s the matter? What       s the matter?       
spluttered Wiley.        Was my speed too much for
you? Couldn       t you see it when it came across?
Shall I pitch you a slow one?       

Hallett shook his head, unable to reply.

       Oh, vurry, vurry well,        said the Marine Marvel.
       As you choose. I don       t want to be too hard
on you.        Then, after going through with a startling
variation of the former convulsions, he did
